px;">The grandfathering provision of the EB-5 Reform and Integrity Act of 2022 establishes September 30, 2026 as a binding legislative deadline. Petitions filed on or before this date carry statutory protection against future program changes. Petitions filed after do not.</p><div style="font-size:9.5px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.26em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;border-bottom:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;padding-bottom:6px;margin-bottom:18px;">Program Timeline</div><div style="position:relative;margin:0 0 30px;padding-left:30px;border-left:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;"><div style="position:relative;margin-bottom:22px;"><div style="position:absolute;left:-34px;top:6px;width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:#1c1a17;"></div><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;margin-bottom:2px;">March 2022</div><div style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1c1a17;margin-bottom:4px;line-height:1.3;">EB-5 Reform & Integrity Act Enacted</div><div style="font-size:14px;color:#4e4c48;line-height:1.65;">Congress reauthorized the Regional Center program with sweeping reforms, introducing reserved visa categories, enhanced escrow requirements, new compliance obligations, and an explicit grandfathering provision tied to a sunset date.</div></div><div style="position:relative;margin-bottom:22px;"><div style="position:absolute;left:-37px;top:4px;width:12px;height:12px;border-radius:50%;background:#fff;border:2px solid #1c1a17;"></div><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;margin-bottom:2px;">May 2026 <span style="display:inline-block;font-size:9px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;border:0.5px solid #1c1a17;color:#1c1a17;padding:1px 5px;margin-left:7px;vertical-align:middle;">Current</span></div><div style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1c1a17;margin-bottom:4px;line-height:1.3;">Optimal Filing Window</div><div style="font-size:14px;color:#4e4c48;line-height:1.65;">Investors who file now benefit from the $800,000 TEA threshold, an earlier visa queue priority date, and the full protection of the grandfathering clause.</div><div style="border-top:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;border-bottom:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;padding:10px 0;margin-top:12px;"><div style="font-size:9px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;margin-bottom:4px;">Practitioner Note</div><div style="font-size:13.5px;font-style:italic;color:#3a3835;line-height:1.6;">Filing before the deadline locks in current investment minimums. USCIS regulations permit inflation-based threshold increases; delay may expose investors to materially higher capital requirements.</div></div></div><div style="position:relative;margin-bottom:22px;"><div style="position:absolute;left:-37px;top:4px;width:12px;height:12px;border-radius:50%;background:#1c1a17;"></div><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;margin-bottom:2px;">September 30, 2026 <span style="display:inline-block;font-size:9px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;border:0.5px solid #1c1a17;color:#1c1a17;padding:1px 5px;margin-left:7px;vertical-align:middle;">Statutory Deadline</span></div><div style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1c1a17;margin-bottom:4px;line-height:1.3;">Last Date for Grandfathering Protection</div><div style="font-size:14px;color:#4e4c48;line-height:1.65;">The grandfathering provision expires. USCIS must continue adjudicating petitions filed on or before this date regardless of subsequent legislative action. No equivalent protection exists for later filings.</div><div style="border-top:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;border-bottom:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;padding:10px 0;margin-top:12px;"><div style="font-size:9px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;margin-bottom:4px;">Legislative Risk</div><div style="font-size:13.5px;font-style:italic;color:#3a3835;line-height:1.6;">If Congress fails to reauthorize the program or does so under amended terms, petitions filed after this date may be suspended, denied, or subject to requirements not in effect at the time of filing.</div></div></div><div style="position:relative;margin-bottom:22px;"><div style="position:absolute;left:-34px;top:6px;width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:#fff;border:1px solid #9a9690;"></div><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;margin-bottom:2px;">October 2026 – September 2027</div><div style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1c1a17;margin-bottom:4px;line-height:1.3;">Congressional Reauthorization Period</div><div style="font-size:14px;color:#4e4c48;line-height:1.65;">Congress must vote to reauthorize the program before September 30, 2027. Terms, including thresholds and set-aside allocations, are subject to legislative discretion. Investors who filed before October 1, 2026 are shielded from this uncertainty.</div></div><div style="position:relative;"><div style="position:absolute;left:-34px;top:6px;width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:#fff;border:1px solid #9a9690;"></div><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;margin-bottom:2px;">September 30, 2027</div><div style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1c1a17;margin-bottom:4px;line-height:1.3;">Program Authorization Expiration</div><div style="font-size:14px;color:#4e4c48;line-height:1.65;">The RIA program authorization lapses. Investors who filed after September 30, 2026 are subject to whatever terms Congress establishes, or to program suspension if reauthorization does not occur.</div></div></div><div style="font-size:9.5px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.26em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;border-bottom:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;padding-bottom:6px;margin-bottom:14px;">Key Facts</div><table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-bottom:8px;"><thead><tr><th style="font-size:9.5px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;text-align:left;padding:0 0 8px;border-bottom:1.5px solid #1c1a17;width:36%;">Item</th><th style="font-size:9.5px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8a8578;text-align:left;padding:0 0 8px;border-bottom:1.5px solid #1c1a17;">Detail</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style="font-size:14px;color:#1c1a17;font-weight:500;padding:9px 16px 9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">Deadline date</td><td style="font-size:14px;color:#3a3835;padding:9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">September 30, 2026 — petitions must be filed with USCIS</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:14px;color:#1c1a17;font-weight:500;padding:9px 16px 9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">Governing provision</td><td style="font-size:14px;color:#3a3835;padding:9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">EB-5 Reform and Integrity Act of 2022, grandfathering clause</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:14px;color:#1c1a17;font-weight:500;padding:9px 16px 9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">TEA investment minimum</td><td style="font-size:14px;color:#3a3835;padding:9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">$800,000 (Targeted Employment Area projects)</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:14px;color:#1c1a17;font-weight:500;padding:9px 16px 9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">Standard investment</td><td style="font-size:14px;color:#3a3835;padding:9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">$1,050,000 (non-TEA projects)</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:14px;color:#1c1a17;font-weight:500;padding:9px 16px 9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">Reauthorization deadline</td><td style="font-size:14px;color:#3a3835;padding:9px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid #dedad3;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">September 30, 2027</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:14px;color:#1c1a17;font-weight:500;padding:9px 0 9px 0;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">Protection for post-deadline filers</td><td style="font-size:14px;color:#3a3835;padding:9px 0;vertical-align:top;line-height:1.5;">None under current statutory framework</td></tr></tbody></table></div><figcaption style="margin:0 28px;padding:14px 0 22px;border-top:0.5px solid #d0ccc4;font-size:11px;font-style:italic;color:#8a8578;line-height:1.6;">For educational purposes only. Not legal or investment advice. Consult a licensed immigration attorney and FINRA-registered advisor before making any filing or investment decisions.</figcaption></figure>

### The Strategic Advantage of Filing Early

Sophisticated investors are moving quickly to secure their petitions. Filing early not only locks in current regulations and investment amounts but also provides a strategic advantage in the visa queue.

As the deadline approaches a surge in demand is inevitable. This surge will likely lead to increased competition for high-quality projects, capacity constraints at regional centers and longer USCIS processing times. By initiating the process now, investors can avoid these bottlenecks and secure an earlier priority date. This is particularly important for individuals from countries that may face future visa retrogression as an earlier priority date can significantly reduce the overall wait time for a green card.

Early filing allows investors to take advantage of the current investment thresholds. The RIA includes provisions for inflation-based increases to the minimum investment amounts in the future. By filing before the deadline, investors can ensure they are subject to the current financial requirements instead of the future increased amount which could potentially save the investor hundreds of thousands of dollars.

## Conclusion

The EB-5 immigrant investor program remains a powerful and viable tool for families in Africa and the MENA region seeking stability, educational opportunities and global mobility. The reforms introduced by the RIA have strengthened the program and provided greater transparency, enhanced investor protections and expedited processing for certain project categories. Success in the post-RIA landscape requires planning, sufficient documentation and a clear understanding of regulatory deadlines.

For families considering the EB-5 program in the near future the prep work must begin immediately. This involves clarifying priorities, engaging experienced immigration counsel and conducting substantial due diligence. Investors must carefully evaluate potential projects, prioritizing job creation and capital safety over speculative financial returns.

By taking a sequential, well-structured approach and acting before the critical September 30, 2026 deadline, investors can navigate the complexities of the EB-5 program with confidence. The EB-5 program is a strategic decision that can secure a lasting legacy and exciting opportunities for future African and MENA generations in the United States.

